@1062 = ~Buckler~
@1063 = ~The Leafrunner +3~
@1064 = ~This buckler is known as The Leafrunner. It was once used by a druid-protector known as Blasanna Leafrunner, and the item was named after her family name. One day, she had to defent her beloved grove and her family from a group of a gnoll army. The tales say that during the fight, she moved as quickly as a lightning, and she defeated half of the army herself. Rest of the gnolls run away, but she became a local hero.
  
Some suggest that her rapid moves were a result of holding this powerful buckler. Others say that it was nature that had her back, pushing her forward, no matter what. Some also say that those that wield this weapon can protect themselves fith wall of energy.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– May cast Sanctuary once per day (on self)

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +4
– Grants only half of the Armor Class bonus vs. missiles and piercing attacks
– Doubles movement rate
– Saving Throws vs. Ivocation School: +2

Requires:
 4 Strength

Weight: 2~
@1065 = ~Herbal Brew in a Mug~
@1066 = ~This brew is made of chamomile, wild honey, blackberry and lavender. It's supposed to calm people down.
  
STATISTICS: 

Weight: 2~
@1067 = ~Delgorth's Note~
@1068 = ~First Entry:
The Vesper Vein... the legends were true. It blooms still amidst the shattered remnants of Myth Unnohyr, where dead magic festers and life warps. Each petal hums with quiet malice, steeped in a power neither divine nor mortal. Talona smiles upon my discovery.

Second Entry:
With painstaking effort, I have distilled the first batches of the toxin. Small quantities only—precious drops of death, born of the Vein’s purple heart. Already, the results have exceeded expectations: swift, incurable, a silencer of both flesh and spirit.

Third Entry:
My first shipments have been delivered to certain enemies of the Harpers. Petty lords, disillusioned sellswords, and those who see the Harpers' meddling as a threat to true balance. Let the self-righteous choke on their piousness.

Fourth Entry:
The Night Masks in Westgate see potential. They offer coin and bodies to spread the work, but they lack subtlety. I must tread carefully. The Zhentarim, ever watchful, may prove useful—if kept at arm’s length.

Fifth Entry:
The foundations here in Myth Unnohyr are firm enough—its wild and dead magic shields my work from unwanted eyes. Though I have managed to cultivate a few vines within the dead soil, they grow slowly, stubbornly, yielding but scant blossoms. At this rate, it will take seasons to produce enough toxin for the ambitions I nurture. I must seek a way to quicken their growth—or secure more hands willing to tend the cursed harvest.

Sixth Entry:
This Eldathyn interfered, and paid for his foolishness. Others may come, but the path is clear: the toxin will spread. It will seep into the veins of Faerûn’s mighty and humble alike. Talona’s will is woven into every trembling breath they take.

Let the strong fall and the weak wither. Only decay is eternal!
May all who breathe know suffering—and in their final, gasping moments, know Her name.

— Malagent Delgorth
~
@1071 = ~Longsword~
@1072 = ~The Remembrance of the Myths +5~
@1073 = ~This blade once belonged to an elven knight, a hunter of the undead. The tales say that it was used in many battles and managed to pierce from armors and spells of vampires, liches, skeletal warriors and even was used in a fight agains a dracolich. It was during that battle, however, when the creature used all its power to smash the blade. The faith and the magic locked inside the blade manifested in a form of a spectral blade.

From that day, the sword is no longer able to harm the living, but the spectral blade became even more powerful against undead enemies. It is able to hurt both corporeal and incorporeal monsters, as long as there is some undead woven into their existance. 

For many years, the blade was lost, only to be found at the Duskwood Dell and given to <CHARNAME> so <PRO_HESHE> could use this weapon agains powerful undead monsters.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– May cast False Dawn once per day

Equipped abilities:
– Infravision
– Armor Class vs. Undead: +2
– Saving Throws vs. Undead: +2
– Turn Undead level: +2 (paladins and clerics only)

Combat abilities:
– Cannot harm any living creature, only the undead
– Does not receive bonus damage from strength and critical hits does not deal any bonus damage
– Has a 20% chance that an undead enemy hit by this weapon will suffer additional 2d8+5 fire damage (Save vs. Spells -5 to halve the damage)
– Has a 10% chance that an undead enemy hit by this weapon will be instantly destroyed 

THAC0: +5
Damage: 2d8+5 (magic)
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 2
~

@1075 = ~Headband~
@1076 = ~Halo of Corrosive Blood~
@1077 = ~This powerful is a crown made of congealed blood. It was previously worn by a powerful monster imprisoned under Myth Unnohyr - an elder blood amniote.
  
This magical halo may be used to spread a "gift" of corrosion, resulting in great pain and... to some it may be nothing less than a gift of death.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– May cast Dolorous Decay once per day

Equipped abilities:
– Charisma: -1
– Acid Resistance: +10%
– There is a 25% chance that an attacker that succefully hits the wearer of this item will suffer 1d2 acid damage (Death Save -2 to negate)
– May only be removed with a Remove Curse spell

Weight: 1
~
@1078 = ~Dagger~
@1079 = ~Scolopendra's Spit +3~
@1080 = ~This powerful dagger is an ideal weapon for spellcasters, especially those that specialize in summonig all sorts of acidic creations and projectiles. It does not only improve caster's abilities, but also allows such adventurers to attack enemies from a distance.

STATISTICS:

