~
@1087 = ~Rose of Eldath~
@1088 = ~This is a rose blossom, blessed by a priest of Eldath. Those that consume this flower are healed from the horrible effects of all usual poisons and heals over time.
  
STATISTICS:

Special: Cures poison and heals 6 Hit Points over 1 round

Weight: 1~
@1089 = ~Two-Handed Sword~
@1090 = ~Good Luck, Honeysuckle +4~
@1091 = ~This powerful two-handed sword was once used by a ranger named Vala'll Stormneedle, a man known by all living near Larswood. He had a perfect life, perfect family, and a kind and loving wife, warioress Systianna. Each time Vala'll would live on a mission, she would kiss him in a cheek and tell him "good luck, honeysuckly" and would handle him his sord. Legends say that unlike many heroes, he managed to live up until they were both eighty years old. It was then that he lost his life to pneumonia.

Some say that it is this sword that let him live for so long for ordinary human standards and those that spend most of their lives with a sword in their hands.
  
STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Luck: +1
– Constitution: +1
– Missile Damage resistance: +20% (rangers only)

Combat abilities:
– Each succesful hit has a 15% chance to lower target's luck by 1 point for 2 rounds (Save vs. Spell -4 to negate)

THAC0: +4
Damage: 1d10+4 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Two-handed Sword
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 14 Strength

Weight: 9~
