Proficiency Type: Crossbow
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 8 Strength

Weight: 6~
@1095 = ~Hide Armor~
@1096 = ~4th Beast's Hide +3~
@1097 = ~This magic hide armor was created from scraps of different scraps of animals: pelt of a winter wold, strengthened with parts of ankheg shell and wyvern scales. While the hide is the main part of the armor, and the other two seem to be used for the sake of it's durability and look, it's all been merged together with raw magic. 

What is the fourth beast, if it's made mostly with parts of three different creatures? Well, the fourth beast is the one that wears it, as only such a person would be eager to wear this prmitive and somewhat bloody armor made of different scraps. No matter how powerful it is.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
– Once per day may summon one random creature (winter wolf, ankheg or baby wyvern)

Combat abilities:
– Physical damage resistance: +5%
– Each succeful hit made against the wearer of the armor has 40% chance to apply +1 THAC0 bonus for 1 round (cumulative)

Equipped abilities:
– Open Locks: -10%
– Find Traps: -10%
– Pick Pockets: -10%
– Move Silently: -20%

Armor Class: 3 (5 vs. piercing and missile)
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 35~
@1098 = ~Create Mystic Candle~
@1099 = ~Create Mystic Candle
(Evocation)

Level: 5
Range: 0
Duration: 24 hours
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows the caster to create one Mystic Candle that is able to hold special enchantment which may be trigger when the candle it used. That means the caster may use some power and other ingredients to store it in a form of a candle for later use. Each color candle has different effects:

Red - Charm Person or Mammal
Blue - Protection from Evil, 10' radius
Purple - Know Alignment  
Gold - Cure Medium Wounds
Yellow - Command
Green - Luck
White - Neutralize Poison
Silver - Draw Upon Holy Might
Black - Doom

The candle may be used by the caster or another character, provided they have at least 12 or more Wisdom. After twenty four hours passes, the candle is destroyed.

* * *

Note: This spell may be learned by mages, clerics and druids. Clerics and druids can learn it by using it through quick slot items. This spell cannot be cast from a scroll.
~
